	bool readwrite local 001312D4
"Specifies whether to enable or disable the RF output signal.
VI_TRUE 1
True

VI_FALSE 0
False"
attribute: "AM Enabled [AM]"
	"Analog Modulation:AM:AM Enabled [AM]"
	bool readwrite local 001312DB
"Specifies whether the signal generator applies amplitude modulation to the RF output signal (TRUE) or not (FALSE).
VI_TRUE 1
True

VI_FALSE 0
False"
attribute: "AM Source [AM]"
	"Analog Modulation:AM:AM Source [AM]"
	string readwrite local 001312DC
"Specifies the source of the signal that is used as the modulating signal. If more than one source is specified, the voltages of all sources (internal and external) are summed.  Multiple source names are separated by commas."
attribute: "AM Scaling [AM]"
	"Analog Modulation:AM:AM Scaling [AM]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_AM_SCALING_LINEAR=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_AM_SCALING_LOGARITHMIC=2} readwrite local 001312DD
"Specifies linear or logarithmic attenuation for amplitude modulation. The unit of the IviRFSigGen>>Analog Modulation>>AM>>AM Depth [AM] property is changed with this setting.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_AM_SCALING_LINEAR 1
Enables linear attenuation for amplitude modulation.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_AM_SCALING_LOGARITHMIC 2
Enables logarithmic attenuation for amplitude modulation."
attribute: "AM External Coupling [AM]"
	"Analog Modulation:AM:AM External Coupling [AM]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_AM_EXTERNAL_COUPLING_AC=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_AM_EXTERNAL_COUPLING_DC=2} readwrite local 001312DE
"Specifies the coupling of the external source of the modulating signal.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_AM_EXTERNAL_COUPLING_AC 1
The external source is coupled for AC only.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_AM_EXTERNAL_COUPLING_DC 2
The external source is coupled for both DC and AC"
attribute: "AM Nominal Voltage [AM]"
	"Analog Modulation:AM:AM Nominal Voltage [AM]"
	fD readonly local 001312DF
"This is the voltage at which the instrument achieves the amount of modulation specified by the IviRFSigGen>>Analog Modulation>>AM>>AM Depth [AM] property.

Note: This property is read only."
attribute: "AM Depth [AM]"
	"Analog Modulation:AM:AM Depth [AM]"
	fD readwrite local 001312E0
"Specifies the extend of modulation the signal generator applies to the RF-signal (carrier waveform) with the modulating signal as a result of summing all sources, internal and external.
If the IviRFSigGen>>Analog Modulation>>AM>>AM Scaling [AM] property is set to Linear, then the units are percent (%). If the IviRFSigGen>>Analog Modulation>>AM>>AM Scaling [AM] property is set to logarithmic, then the units are dBm."
attribute: "FM Enabled [FM]"
	"Analog Modulation:FM:FM Enabled [FM]"
	bool readwrite local 001312E5
"Specifies whether the signal generator applies frequency modulation to the RF output signal (TRUE) or not (FALSE).
VI_TRUE 1
True

VI_FALSE 0
False"
attribute: "FM Source [FM]"
	"Analog Modulation:FM:FM Source [FM]"
	string readwrite local 001312E6
"Specifies the source of the signal that is used as the modulating signal. If more than one source is specified, the voltages of all sources (internal and external) are summed.  Multiple source names are separated by commas."
attribute: "FM External Coupling [FM]"
	"Analog Modulation:FM:FM External Coupling [FM]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_FM_EXTERNAL_COUPLING_AC=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_FM_EXTERNAL_COUPLING_DC=2} readwrite local 001312E7
"Specifies the coupling of the external source of the modulating signal.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_FM_EXTERNAL_COUPLING_AC 1
The external source is coupled for AC only.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_FM_EXTERNAL_COUPLING_DC 2
The external source is coupled for both DC and AC."
attribute: "FM Nominal Voltage [FM]"
	"Analog Modulation:FM:FM Nominal Voltage [FM]"
	fD readonly local 001312E8
"This is the voltage at which the instrument achieves the amount of modulation specified by the IviRFSigGen>>Analog Modulation>>FM>>FM Deviation [FM] property.

Note: This property is read only."
attribute: "FM Deviation [FM]"
	"Analog Modulation:FM:FM Deviation [FM]"
	fD readwrite local 001312E9
"Specifies the extent of modulation (peak frequency deviation) the signal generator applies to the RF-signal (carrier waveform) with the modulating signal as a result of summing all sources,internal and external. 
The units are Hz."
