	"Analog Modulation:PM:PM Nominal Voltage [PM]"
	fD readonly local 001312F2
"This is the voltage at which the instrument achieves the amount of modulation specified by the IviRFSigGen>>Analog Modulation>>PM>>PM Deviation [PM] property. 

Note: This property is read only."
attribute: "PM Deviation [PM]"
	"Analog Modulation:PM:PM Deviation [PM]"
	fD readwrite local 001312F3
"Specifies the extent of modulation (peak phase deviation) the signal generator applies to the RF-signal (carrier waveform) with the modulating signal. The units are radians."
attribute: "Modulation Source Count [MS]"
	"Analog Modulation:Source:Modulation Source Count [MS]"
	iL readonly local 001312F9
"Specifies how many analog modulation sources are available."
attribute: "Pulse Modulation Enabled [PULM]"
	"Pulse Modulation:Pulse Modulation Enabled [PULM]"
	bool readwrite local 00131303
"Specifies whether the signal generator applies pulse modulation to the RF output signal (TRUE) or not (FALSE).
VI_TRUE 1
True

VI_FALSE 0
False"
attribute: "Pulse Modulation Source [PULM]"
	"Pulse Modulation:Pulse Modulation Source [PULM]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_PULSE_MODULATION_SOURCE_INTERNAL=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_PULSE_MODULATION_SOURCE_EXTERNAL=2} readwrite local 00131304
"Specifies the source of the signal that is used as the modulating signal.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_PULSE_MODULATION_SOURCE_INTERNAL 1
An internal pulse generator (IviRFSigGenPulseGenerator Extension Group) is used for modulation.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_PULSE_MODULATION_SOURCE_EXTERNAL 2
An external generator is used for modulation."
attribute: "Pulse Modulation External Polarity [PULM]"
	"Pulse Modulation:Pulse Modulation External Polarity [PULM]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_PULSE_MODULATION_EXTERNAL_POLARITY_NORMAL=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_PULSE_MODULATION_EXTERNAL_POLARITY_INVERSE=2} readwrite local 00131305
"Specifies the polarity of the external source signal.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_PULSE_MODULATION_EXTERNAL_POLARITY_NORMAL 1
The signal generator modulates the carrier signal with normal pulse polarity.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_PULSE_MODULATION_EXTERNAL_POLARITY_INVERSE 2
The signal generator modulates the carrier signal with inverted pulse polarity."
attribute: "Active LF Generator [LF]"
	"LF Generator:Active LF Generator [LF]"
	string readwrite local 00131335
"Specifies the LF generator which is currently active. The values for this property correspond to the LFGenerator repeated capability."
attribute: "LF Generator Count [LF]"
	"LF Generator:LF Generator Count [LF]"
	iL readonly local 00131338
"Specifies the number of LF generator sources available for a particular instrument."
attribute: "LF Generator Frequency [LF]"
	"LF Generator:LF Generator Frequency [LF]"
	fD readwrite local 00131336
"Specifies the frequency of the active LF generator. The unit is Hz."
attribute: "LF Generator Waveform [LF]"
	"LF Generator:LF Generator Waveform [LF]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_LF_GENERATOR_WAVEFORM_SINE=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_LF_GENERATOR_WAVEFORM_SQUARE=2, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_LF_GENERATOR_WAVEFORM_TRIANGLE=3, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_LF_GENERATOR_WAVEFORM_RAMP_UP=4, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_LF_GENERATOR_WAVEFORM_RAMP_DOWN=5} readwrite local 00131337
"Specifies the waveform of the active LF generator.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_LF_GENERATOR_WAVEFORM_SINE 1
Configures the LF generator to produce a sinusoidal waveform.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_LF_GENERATOR_WAVEFORM_SQUARE 2
Configures the LF generator to produce a square waveform.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_LF_GENERATOR_WAVEFORM_TRIANGLE 3
Configures the LF generator to produce a triangle waveform.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_LF_GENERATOR_WAVEFORM_RAMP_UP 4
Configures the LF generator to produce a rising ramp waveform.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_LF_GENERATOR_WAVEFORM_RAMP_DOWN 5
Configures the LF generator to produce a falling ramp waveform."
attribute: "LF Generator Output Amplitude [LFO]"
	"LF Generator:LF Generator Outputs:LF Generator Output Amplitude [LFO]"
	fD readwrite local 0013133F
"Specifies the output voltage of the LF generator. The unit is V."
attribute: "LF Generator Output Enabled [LFO]"
	"LF Generator:LF Generator Outputs:LF Generator Output Enabled [LFO]"
	bool readwrite local 00131340
"Specifies whether the LF generator applies an output signal (TRUE) or not (FALSE).
VI_TRUE 1
True

VI_FALSE 0
False"
attribute: "Pulse Internal Trigger Period [PG]"
	"Pulse Generator:Pulse Internal Trigger Period [PG]"
	fD readwrite local 00131349
"Specifies the period of the pulse generators output signal (if Pulse Trigger Source is set to Internal). The units are in seconds."
attribute: "Pulse Width [PG]"
	"Pulse Generator:Pulse Width [PG]"
	fD readwrite local 0013134A
"Specifies the width of the output pulse. The units are in seconds."
attribute: "Pulse Gating Enabled [PG]"
	"Pulse Generator:Pulse Gating Enabled [PG]"
	bool readwrite local 0013134B
"Specifies whether pulse gating is enabled(TRUE) or disabled(FALSE).
VI_TRUE 1
True

VI_FALSE 0
False"
attribute: "Pulse Trigger Source [PG]"
	"Pulse Generator:Pulse Trigger Source [PG]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_PULSE_TRIGGER_SOURCE_INTERNAL=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_PULSE_TRIGGER_SOURCE_EXTERNAL=2} readwrite local 0013134C
"Specifies the source of the signal the pulse generator uses to generate one pulse.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_PULSE_TRIGGER_SOURCE_INTERNAL 1
No external trigger is used. The pulse period is specified by the IviRFSigGen>>Pulse Generator>>Pulse Internal Trigger Period [PG] property.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_PULSE_TRIGGER_SOURCE_EXTERNAL 2
The pulse is started with a trigger after the delay time specified by the IviRFSigGen>>Pulse Generator>>Pulse External Trigger Delay [PG] property."
attribute: "Pulse External Trigger Slope [PG]"
	"Pulse Generator:Pulse External Trigger Slope [PG]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_PULSE_EXTERNAL_TRIGGER_SLOPE_POSITIVE=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_PULSE_EXTERNAL_TRIGGER_SLOPE_NEGATIVE=2} readwrite local 0013134D
"Specifies whether the event occurs on the rising or falling edge of the input signal.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_PULSE_EXTERNAL_TRIGGER_SLOPE_POSITIVE 1
Enables rising edge triggering.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_PULSE_EXTERNAL_TRIGGER_SLOPE_NEGATIVE 2
Enables falling edge triggering."
attribute: "Pulse External Trigger Delay [PG]"
	"Pulse Generator:Pulse External Trigger Delay [PG]"
	fD readwrite local 0013134E
"Specifies the delay for starting the output pulse with respect to the trigger input. The units are in seconds."
attribute: "Pulse Double Enabled [DPG]"
	"Pulse Generator:Double Pulse Generators:Pulse Double Enabled [DPG]"
	bool readwrite local 00131353
"Specifies whether double pulse mode is used (TRUE) or not (FALSE).
VI_TRUE 1
True

VI_FALSE 0
False"
attribute: "Pulse Double Delay [DPG]"
	"Pulse Generator:Double Pulse Generators:Pulse Double Delay [DPG]"
	fD readwrite local 00131354
"Specifies the delay of the second pulse. The units are in seconds."
attribute: "Pulse Output Enabled [PGO]"
	"Pulse Generator:Pulse Generator Output:Pulse Output Enabled [PGO]"
	bool readwrite local 0013135E
"Specifies whether the output of the pulse generator is on  (TRUE) or off (FALSE).
VI_TRUE 1
True

VI_FALSE 0
False"
attribute: "Pulse Output Polarity [PGO]"
	"Pulse Generator:Pulse Generator Output:Pulse Output Polarity [PGO]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_PULSE_OUTPUT_POLARITY_NORMAL=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_PULSE_OUTPUT_POLARITY_INVERSE=2} readwrite local 0013135D
"Specifies the polarity of the output signal.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_PULSE_OUTPUT_POLARITY_NORMAL 1
Specifies normal polarity.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_PULSE_OUTPUT_POLARITY_INVERSE 2
Specifies inverted polarity."
attribute: "Sweep Mode [SWP]"
	"Sweep:Sweep Mode [SWP]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_SWEEP_MODE_NONE=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_SWEEP_MODE_FREQUENCY_SWEEP=2, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_SWEEP_MODE_POWER_SWEEP=3, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_SWEEP_MODE_FREQUENCY_STEP=4, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_SWEEP_MODE_POWER_STEP=5, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_SWEEP_MODE_LIST=6} readwrite local 00131399
"Specifies the sweep mode applied to the output signal.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_SWEEP_MODE_NONE 1
The RF output of the signal generator is a non-swept signal (Continuous Wave). Frequency and power level from base capability group is used.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_SWEEP_MODE_FREQUENCY_SWEEP 2
The signal generator sweeps the RF output signal's frequency in an analog form (non-stepped).

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_SWEEP_MODE_POWER_SWEEP 3
The signal generator sweeps the RF output signal's power level in an analog form (non-stepped).

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_SWEEP_MODE_FREQUENCY_STEP 4
The signal generator sweeps the RF output signals frequency in steps.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_SWEEP_MODE_POWER_STEP 5
The signal generator sweeps the RF output signals power level in steps.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_SWEEP_MODE_LIST 6
The signal generator uses two lists with frequency and power level values to sweep the RF output signals."
attribute: "Sweep Trigger Source [SWP]"
	"Sweep:Sweep Trigger Source [SWP]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_SWEEP_TRIGGER_SOURCE_IMMEDIATE=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_SWEEP_TRIGGER_SOURCE_EXTERNAL=2, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_SWEEP_TRIGGER_SOURCE_SOFTWARE=3} readwrite local 0013139A
"Specifies the trigger used to start a sweep operation.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_SWEEP_TRIGGER_SOURCE_IMMEDIATE 1
The sweep system does not wait for a trigger of any kind, so it is running continuously.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_SWEEP_TRIGGER_SOURCE_EXTERNAL 2
The sweep is started with an external signal.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_SWEEP_TRIGGER_SOURCE_SOFTWARE 3
The sweep is started with a software programmable trigger."
attribute: "Frequency Sweep Start [FSW]"
	"Sweep:Frequency Sweep:Frequency Sweep Start [FSW]"
	fD readwrite local 001313A3
"Specifies the start frequency of the sweep. If the stop frequency is less than the start frequency, the frequency decreases during the sweep. The units are in Hz."
attribute: "Frequency Sweep Stop [FSW]"
	"Sweep:Frequency Sweep:Frequency Sweep Stop [FSW]"
	fD readwrite local 001313A4
"Specifies the stop frequency of the sweep. If the stop frequency is less than the start frequency, the frequency decreases during the sweep. The units are in Hz."
attribute: "Frequency Sweep Time [FSW]"
	"Sweep:Frequency Sweep:Frequency Sweep Time [FSW]"
	fD readwrite local 001313A5
"Specifies the duration of one sweep from start to stop frequency. The units are in seconds."
attribute: "Power Sweep Start [PSW]"
	"Sweep:Power Sweep:Power Sweep Start [PSW]"
	fD readwrite local 001313AD
"Specifies the start power of the sweep. If the stop power is less than the start power, the power decreases in value during the sweep. The units are in dBm."
attribute: "Power Sweep Stop [PSW]"
	"Sweep:Power Sweep:Power Sweep Stop [PSW]"
	fD readwrite local 001313AE
"Specifies the stop power of the sweep. If the stop power is less than the start power, the power decreases in value during the sweep. The units are in dBm."
attribute: "Power Sweep Time [PSW]"
	"Sweep:Power Sweep:Power Sweep Time [PSW]"
	fD readwrite local 001313AF
"Specifies the duration of one sweep from start to stop power. The units are in seconds."
attribute: "Frequency Step Start [FST]"
	"Sweep:Frequency Step:Frequency Step Start [FST]"
	fD readwrite local 001313C1
"Specifies the start frequency of the stepped sweep. If the stop frequency is less than the start frequency, the frequency decreases during the sweep. The units are in Hz."
attribute: "Frequency Step Stop [FST]"
	"Sweep:Frequency Step:Frequency Step Stop [FST]"
	fD readwrite local 001313C2
"Specifies the stop frequency of the stepped sweep. If the stop frequency is less than the start frequency, the frequency decreases during the sweep. The units are in Hz."
attribute: "Frequency Step Scaling [FST]"
	"Sweep:Frequency Step:Frequency Step Scaling [FST]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_FREQUENCY_STEP_SCALING_LINEAR=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_FREQUENCY_STEP_SCALING_LOGARITHMIC=2} readwrite local 001313C3
"Specifies the spacing of the steps.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_FREQUENCY_STEP_SCALING_LINEAR 1
Enables linear scaling.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_FREQUENCY_STEP_SCALING_LOGARITHMIC 2
Enables logarithmic scaling."
attribute: "Frequency Step Size [FST]"
	"Sweep:Frequency Step:Frequency Step Size [FST]"
	fD readwrite local 001313C4
"Specifies the step size. The units are in Hz when the IviRFSigGen>>Sweep>>Frequency Step>>Frequency Step Scaling [FST] property is set to IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_FREQUENCY_STEP_SCALING_LINEAR. 
The value is unitless (factor) when the  IviRFSigGen>>Sweep>>Frequency Step>>Frequency Step Scaling [FST] property is set to IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_FREQUENCY_STEP_SCALING_LOGARITHMIC."
attribute: "Frequency Step Single Step Enabled [FST]"
	"Sweep:Frequency Step:Frequency Step Single Step Enabled [FST]"
	bool readwrite local 001313C5
"Specifies whether the trigger initiates the next step (TRUE), or the next step is taken after dwell time (FALSE).
VI_TRUE 1
True

VI_FALSE 0
False"
attribute: "Frequency Step Dwell [FST]"
	"Sweep:Frequency Step:Frequency Step Dwell [FST]"
	fD readwrite local 001313C6
"Specifies the duration time of one step. The units are in seconds.
Dwell time starts immediate after tigger or next step; no settling time is added.
This property is ignored if Frequency Step Single Step Enabled is set to TRUE."
attribute: "Power Step Start [PST]"
	"Sweep:Power Step:Power Step Start [PST]"
	fD readwrite local 001313D5
"Specifies the start power of the stepped sweep. If the stop power is less than the start power, the power decreases in value during the sweep. The units are in dBm."
attribute: "Power Step Stop [PST]"
	"Sweep:Power Step:Power Step Stop [PST]"
	fD readwrite local 001313D6
"Specifies the stop power of the stepped sweep. If the stop power is less than the start power, the power decreases in value during the sweep. The units are in dBm."
attribute: "Power Step Size [PST]"
	"Sweep:Power Step:Power Step Size [PST]"
	fD readwrite local 001313D7
"Specifies the step size. The units are in dBm."
attribute: "Single Step Enabled [PST]"
	"Sweep:Power Step:Single Step Enabled [PST]"
	bool readwrite local 001313D8
"Specifies whether the trigger initiates the next step (TRUE), or the next step is taken after dwell time (FALSE).
VI_TRUE 1
True

VI_FALSE 0
False"
attribute: "Power Step Dwell [PST]"
	"Sweep:Power Step:Power Step Dwell [PST]"
	fD readwrite local 001313D9
"Specifies the duration time of one step. The units are in seconds.
This property is ignored if Frequency Step Single Step Enabled is set to TRUE."
attribute: "List Selected Name [LST]"
	"Sweep:List:List Selected Name [LST]"
	string readwrite local 001313E9
"Specifies the name of the selected list to become active. The name must be one of the lists created ."
attribute: "List Single Step Enabled [LST]"
	"Sweep:List:List Single Step Enabled [LST]"
	bool readwrite local 001313EA
"Enables or disables single step mode.
TRUE: The list will advance when the next trigger event occurs.
FALSE: The list will advance immediatly after the dwell time ends.
VI_TRUE 1
True

VI_FALSE 0
False"
attribute: "List Dwell [LST]"
	"Sweep:List:List Dwell [LST]"
	fD readwrite local 001313EB
"Specifies the duration time of one step. The units are in seconds.
This property is ignored if List Single Step Enabled is set to TRUE."
attribute: "ALC Source [ALC]"
	"ALC:ALC Source [ALC]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_ALC_SOURCE_INTERNAL=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_ALC_SOURCE_EXTERNAL=2} readwrite local 001313FD
"Specifies the source of the controlling voltage for the Automatic Level Control.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_ALC_SOURCE_INTERNAL 1
The ALC is controlled by an internal measurement source.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_ALC_SOURCE_EXTERNAL 2
The ALC is controlled by an external voltage."
attribute: "ALC Bandwidth [ALC]"
	"ALC:ALC Bandwidth [ALC]"
	fD readwrite local 001313FE
"Specifies the bandwidth of Automatic Level Control."
attribute: "Reference Oscillator Source [RO]"
	"Reference Oscillator:Reference Oscillator Source [RO]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_REFERENCE_OSCILLATOR_SOURCE_INTERNAL=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_REFERENCE_OSCILLATOR_SOURCE_EXTERNAL=2} readwrite local 00131411
"Specifies the reference frequency source used to generate the exact RF output frequency.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_REFERENCE_OSCILLATOR_SOURCE_INTERNAL 1
An internal reference oscillator is used.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_REFERENCE_OSCILLATOR_SOURCE_EXTERNAL 2
An external reference oscillator is used."
attribute: "Reference Oscillator External Frequency [RO]"
	"Reference Oscillator:Reference Oscillator External Frequency [RO]"
	fD readwrite local 00131412
"Specifies the frequency of the external signal, which is used as reference for internal RF frequency generation. This value is used only if the IviRFSigGen>>Reference Oscillator>>Reference Oscillator Source [RO] property is set to External."
attribute: "IQ Enabled [MIQ]"
	"IQ:IQ Enabled [MIQ]"
	bool readwrite local 00131461
"Specifies whether the signal generator applies IQ (vector) modulation to the output RF signal (TRUE) or not (FALSE).
VI_TRUE 1
True

VI_FALSE 0
False"
attribute: "IQ Nominal Voltage [MIQ]"
	"IQ:IQ Nominal Voltage [MIQ]"
	fD readonly local 00131462
"This is the voltage at which the instrument achieves full modulation. The value is calculated by SQRT(I^2+Q^2)."
attribute: "IQ Source [MIQ]"
	"IQ:IQ Source [MIQ]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_IQ_SOURCE_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_IQ_SOURCE_CDMA_BASE=2, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_IQ_SOURCE_TDMA_BASE=3, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_IQ_SOURCE_ARB_GENERATOR=4, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_IQ_SOURCE_EXTERNAL=5} readwrite local 00131463
"Specifies the source of the signal that the signal generator uses for IQ modulation.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_IQ_SOURCE_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE 1
The signal generator uses the internally generated digital modulation signal to apply IQ modulation to the output RF signal.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_IQ_SOURCE_CDMA_BASE 2
The signal generator uses the internally generated CDMA signal to apply IQ modulation to the output RF signal.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_IQ_SOURCE_TDMA_BASE 3
The signal generator uses the internally generated TDMA signal to apply IQ modulation to the output RF signal.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_IQ_SOURCE_ARB_GENERATOR 4
The signal generator uses the internally generated Arb signal to apply IQ modulation to the output RF signal.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_IQ_SOURCE_EXTERNAL 5
The signal generator uses data from an external source for IQ modulation."
attribute: "IQSwap Enabled [MIQ]"
	"IQ:IQSwap Enabled [MIQ]"
	bool readwrite local 00131464
"Enables or disables the inverse phase rotation of the IQ signal by swapping the I and Q inputs.  If TRUE, the RF signal generator applies non-inverse phase rotation of the IQ signal.  If FALSE, the RF signal generator applies inverse phase rotation of the IQ signal.
VI_TRUE 1
True

VI_FALSE 0
False"
attribute: "IQ Impairment Enabled [IQI]"
	"IQ:IQ Impairment:IQ Impairment Enabled [IQI]"
	bool readwrite local 00131475
"Enables IQ impairment. When set to TRUE, the following impairment properties are applied.
 
IviRFSigGen>>IQ>>IQ Impairment>>IQ I-Offset [IQI]
IviRFSigGen>>IQ>>IQ Impairment>>IQ Q-Offset [IQI]
IviRFSigGen>>IQ>>IQ Impairment>>IQ Ratio [IQI]
IviRFSigGen>>IQ>>IQ Impairment>>IQ Skew [IQI]
VI_TRUE 1
True

VI_FALSE 0
False"
attribute: "IQ I Offset [IQI]"
	"IQ:IQ Impairment:IQ I Offset [IQI]"
	fD readwrite local 00131476
"Specifies an origin offset voltage to the I signal. The range of values allowed is -100% to +100%. The value is expressed as percentage (%)."
attribute: "IQ Q Offset [IQI]"
	"IQ:IQ Impairment:IQ Q Offset [IQI]"
	fD readwrite local 00131477
"Specifies an origin offset voltage to the Q signal. The range of values allowed is -100% to +100%. The value is expressed as percentage (%)."
attribute: "IQ Ratio [IQI]"
	"IQ:IQ Impairment:IQ Ratio [IQI]"
	fD readwrite local 00131478
"Specifies the gain imbalance between the I and Q channels. For no imbalance this value is set to 0 %. The value is expressed as percentage (%)."
attribute: "IQ Skew [IQI]"
	"IQ:IQ Impairment:IQ Skew [IQI]"
	fD readwrite local 00131479
"Specifies the adjustment of the phase angle between the I and Q vectors. If this skew is zero, the phase angle is 90 degrees. The units are degrees."
attribute: "ARB Clock Frequency [ARB]"
	"ARB Generator:ARB Clock Frequency [ARB]"
	fD readwrite local 00131494
"Specifies the sample frequency. The waveform is generated with this clock frequency."
attribute: "ARB Filter Frequency [ARB]"
	"ARB Generator:ARB Filter Frequency [ARB]"
	fD readwrite local 00131495
"Specifies the cut-off frequency of the low pass filter. The waveform is filtered before output with this filter for antialiasing. The filter frequency normally is lower than the clock frequency. The units are Hertz."
attribute: "ARB Selected Waveform [ARB]"
	"ARB Generator:Waveform:ARB Selected Waveform [ARB]"
	string readwrite local 00131493
"Specifies the selected waveform from the pool of available waveforms."
attribute: "ARB Max Number Waveforms [ARB]"
	"ARB Generator:Waveform:ARB Max Number Waveforms [ARB]"
	iL readonly local 00131496
"Returns the max number of waveforms the instrument can hold in the memory. The number may depend on the length of the waveform already in the pool of waveforms saved in the instrument. "
attribute: "ARB Waveform Quantum [ARB]"
	"ARB Generator:Waveform:ARB Waveform Quantum [ARB]"
	iL readonly local 00131497
"Returns the waveform quantum where the waveform length is a multiple of this quantum. If the waveform quantum is 1, there is no restriction on the waveform length other than min and max size."
attribute: "ARB Waveform Size Min [ARB]"
	"ARB Generator:Waveform:ARB Waveform Size Min [ARB]"
	iL readwrite local 00131498
"Returns the minimum size of the waveform length in number of samples. The waveform length must equal or greater than this minimum size. If the minimum size is 1, there is no restriction on the waveform length other than max size and quantum."
attribute: "ARB Waveform Size Max [ARB]"
	"ARB Generator:Waveform:ARB Waveform Size Max [ARB]"
	iL readonly local 00131499
"Returns the maximum waveform length in the number of samples. The waveform length must be equal or less than this maximum size."
attribute: "ARB Trigger Source [ARB]"
	"ARB Generator:Trigger:ARB Trigger Source [ARB]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_ARB_TRIGGER_SOURCE_IMMEDIATE=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_ARB_TRIGGER_SOURCE_EXTERNAL=2, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_ARB_TRIGGER_SOURCE_SOFTWARE=3} readwrite local 0013149A
"Specifies how the Arb waveform is started (triggered).
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_ARB_TRIGGER_SOURCE_IMMEDIATE 1
The ARB generator system does not wait for a trigger. The ARB runs continuously.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_ARB_TRIGGER_SOURCE_EXTERNAL 2
The sweep is started with an external signal.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_ARB_TRIGGER_SOURCE_SOFTWARE 3
The sweep is started with a software programmable trigger."
attribute: "ARB External Trigger Slope [ARB]"
	"ARB Generator:Trigger:ARB External Trigger Slope [ARB]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_ARB_EXTERNAL_TRIGGER_SLOPE_POSITIVE=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_ARB_EXTERNAL_TRIGGER_SLOPE_NEGATIVE=2} readwrite local 0013149B
"Specifies whether the trigger event occurs on the rising or falling edge of the input signal.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_ARB_EXTERNAL_TRIGGER_SLOPE_POSITIVE 1
Enables rising edge triggering.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_ARB_EXTERNAL_TRIGGER_SLOPE_NEGATIVE 2
Enables falling edge triggering."
attribute: "DigitalModulationBase Standard Count [DMB]"
	"Digital Modulation:DigitalModulationBase Standard Count [DMB]"
	iL readonly local 001314C5
"Specifies the number of DigitalModulationBase standards available for a particular instrument."
attribute: "DigitalModulationBase Selected Standard [DMB]"
	"Digital Modulation:DigitalModulationBase Selected Standard [DMB]"
	string readwrite local 001314C6
"Specifies the actual standard used by the instrument. The coding, mapping, symbol rate or bit clock frequency, filter together with the according filter parameters, FSK deviation or ASK depth (in case of FSK or ASK modulation) are set as defined in the selected standard. "
attribute: "DigitalModulationBase Data Source [DMB]"
	"Digital Modulation:DigitalModulationBase Data Source [DMB]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_DATA_SOURCE_EXTERNAL=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_DATA_SOURCE_PRBS=2, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_DATA_SOURCE_BIT_SEQUENCE=3} readwrite local 001314C7
"Specifies the source of data. The data is used to modulate the RF signal according to the standard selected with the DigitalModulationBase Selected Standard property.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_DATA_SOURCE_EXTERNAL 1
The data from an external device connected to the instrument is used.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_DATA_SOURCE_PRBS 2
The internal PRBS (Pseudo Random Binary Sequence) generator is used as data source.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_DATA_SOURCE_BIT_SEQUENCE 3
A constant bit sequence is used as data source and repeated continuously."
attribute: "DigitalModulationBase PRBS Type [DMB]"
	"Digital Modulation:DigitalModulationBase PRBS Type [DMB]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_PRBS_TYPE_PRBS9=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_PRBS_TYPE_PRBS11=2, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_PRBS_TYPE_PRBS15=3, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_PRBS_TYPE_PRBS16=4, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_PRBS_TYPE_PRBS20=5, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_PRBS_TYPE_PRBS21=6, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_PRBS_TYPE_PRBS23=7} readwrite local 001314C8
"Specifies the type of the PRBS as defined in the CCITT-V.52 standard. The PRBS (Pseudo Random Binary Sequence) is used only if DigitalModulationBase Data Source is set to PRBS.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_PRBS_TYPE_PRBS9 1
Length of PRBS sequence is 2^9 -1.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_PRBS_TYPE_PRBS11 2
Length of PRBS sequence is 2^11 -1.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_PRBS_TYPE_PRBS15 3
Length of PRBS sequence is 2^15 -1.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_PRBS_TYPE_PRBS16 4
Length of PRBS sequence is 2^16 -1.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_PRBS_TYPE_PRBS20 5
Length of PRBS sequence is 2^20 -1.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_PRBS_TYPE_PRBS21 6
Length of PRBS sequence is 2^21 -1.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_PRBS_TYPE_PRBS23 7
Length of PRBS sequence is 2^23 -1."
attribute: "DigitalModulationBase Selected Bit Sequence [DMB]"
	"Digital Modulation:DigitalModulationBase Selected Bit Sequence [DMB]"
	string readwrite local 001314C9
"Specifies name of the bit sequence (stream) used as data for digital modulation. The sequence is used only if DigitalModulationBase Data Source is set to BitSequence."
attribute: "DigitalModulationBase Clock Source [DMB]"
	"Digital Modulation:DigitalModulationBase Clock Source [DMB]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_CLOCK_SOURCE_INTERNAL=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_CLOCK_SOURCE_EXTERNAL=2} readwrite local 001314CA
"Specifies the source of the clock signal used to generate the digital modulation according to the selected standard.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_CLOCK_SOURCE_INTERNAL 1
An internal clock generator is used.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_CLOCK_SOURCE_EXTERNAL 2
A connected external clock generator (bit or symbol clock frequency) is used."
attribute: "DigitalModulationBase External Clock Type [DMB]"
	"Digital Modulation:DigitalModulationBase External Clock Type [DMB]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_EXTERNAL_CLOCK_TYPE_BIT=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_EXTERNAL_CLOCK_TYPE_SYMBOL=2} readwrite local 001314CB
"Specifies the type of the external clock signal used to generate the digital modulation. This value is used only if the DigitalModulationBase Clock Source property is set to External.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_EXTERNAL_CLOCK_TYPE_BIT 1
The external clock frequency is equal to the bit clock frequency of the digital modulation.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_DIGITAL_MODULATION_BASE_EXTERNAL_CLOCK_TYPE_SYMBOL 2
The external clock frequency is equal to the symbol clock frequency of the digital modulation."
attribute: "CDMA Standard Count [CDMA]"
