	"CDMA:CDMA Selected Standard [CDMA]"
	string readwrite local 0013152A
"Specifies the actual standard used by the instrument. The modulation type, bit clock frequency and filter together with the according filter parameters are set as defined in the selected standard."
attribute: "CDMA Test Model Count [CDMA]"
	"CDMA:CDMA Test Model Count [CDMA]"
	iL readonly local 0013152D
"Returns the number of CDMA test models available for a particular instrument."
attribute: "CDMA Selected Test Model [CDMA]"
	"CDMA:CDMA Selected Test Model [CDMA]"
	string readwrite local 0013152E
"Specifies the actual CDMA test model used by the instrument."
attribute: "CDMA Clock Source [CDMA]"
	"CDMA:CDMA Clock Source [CDMA]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_CDMA_CLOCK_SOURCE_INTERNAL=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_CDMA_CLOCK_SOURCE_EXTERNAL=2} readwrite local 0013152F
"Specifies the source of the clock signal used to generate the digital modulation according to the selected standard.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_CDMA_CLOCK_SOURCE_INTERNAL 1
The internal clock generator is used.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_CDMA_CLOCK_SOURCE_EXTERNAL 2
A connected external clock generator (bit or symbol clock frequency) is used."
attribute: "CDMA Trigger Source [CDMA]"
	"CDMA:Trigger:CDMA Trigger Source [CDMA]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_CDMA_TRIGGER_SOURCE_IMMEDIATE=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_CDMA_TRIGGER_SOURCE_EXTERNAL=2, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_CDMA_TRIGGER_SOURCE_SOFTWARE=3} readwrite local 0013152B
"Specifies the source of the trigger signal that starts the channel coding generation.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_CDMA_TRIGGER_SOURCE_IMMEDIATE 1
The CDMA generator system does not wait for a trigger. Each channel coding is run continuously.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_CDMA_TRIGGER_SOURCE_EXTERNAL 2
Each channel coding is started with an external signal.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_CDMA_TRIGGER_SOURCE_SOFTWARE 3
Each channel coding is started with a software programmable trigger."
attribute: "CDMA External Trigger Slope [CDMA]"
	"CDMA:Trigger:CDMA External Trigger Slope [CDMA]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_CDMA_EXTERNAL_TRIGGER_SLOPE_POSITIVE=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_CDMA_EXTERNAL_TRIGGER_SLOPE_NEGATIVE=2} readwrite local 0013152C
"Specifies whether the trigger event occurs on the rising or falling edge of the input signal.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_CDMA_EXTERNAL_TRIGGER_SLOPE_POSITIVE 1
Enables rising edge triggering.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_CDMA_EXTERNAL_TRIGGER_SLOPE_NEGATIVE 2
Enables falling edge triggering."
attribute: "TDMA Standard Count [TDMA]"
	"TDMA:TDMA Standard Count [TDMA]"
	iL readonly local 0013158D
"Specifies the number of TDMA standards available for a particular instrument. "
attribute: "TDMA Selected Standard [TDMA]"
	"TDMA:TDMA Selected Standard [TDMA]"
	string readwrite local 0013158E
"Specifies the actual standard used by the instrument. The coding, mapping, symbol rate or bit clock frequency, filter together with the according filter parameters, FSK deviation or ASK depth (in case of FSK or ASK modulation) are set as defined in the selected standard."
attribute: "TDMA Frame Count [TDMA]"
	"TDMA:TDMA Frame Count [TDMA]"
	iL readonly local 00131591
"Specifies the number of TDMA frames available for a particular instrument."
attribute: "TDMA Selected Frame [TDMA]"
	"TDMA:TDMA Selected Frame [TDMA]"
	string readwrite local 00131592
"Specifies the actual frame used by the instrument. It is selected from the list queried with the Get TDMA Frame Names VI."
attribute: "TDMA Clock Source [TDMA]"
	"TDMA:TDMA Clock Source [TDMA]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_TDMA_CLOCK_SOURCE_INTERNAL=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_TDMA_CLOCK_SOURCE_EXTERNAL=2} readwrite local 00131593
"Specifies the source of the clock signal used to generate the digital modulation according to the selected standard.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_TDMA_CLOCK_SOURCE_INTERNAL 1
The internal clock generator is used.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_TDMA_CLOCK_SOURCE_EXTERNAL 2
A connected external clock generator (bit or symbol clock frequency) is used."
attribute: "TDMA Clock Type [TDMA]"
	"TDMA:TDMA Clock Type [TDMA]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_TDMA_EXTERNAL_CLOCK_TYPE_BIT=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_TDMA_EXTERNAL_CLOCK_TYPE_SYMBOL=2} readwrite local 00131594
"Specifies the type of the external clock signal used to generate the digital modulation. This value is used only if the IviRFSigGen>>TDMA>>TDMA Clock Source [TDMA] property is set to External.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_TDMA_EXTERNAL_CLOCK_TYPE_BIT 1
The external clock frequency is equal to the bit clock frequency of the digital modulation.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_TDMA_EXTERNAL_CLOCK_TYPE_SYMBOL 2
The external clock frequency is equal to the symbol clock frequency of the digital modulation."
attribute: "TDMA Trigger Source [TDMA]"
	"TDMA:Trigger:TDMA Trigger Source [TDMA]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_TDMA_TRIGGER_SOURCE_IMMEDIATE=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_TDMA_TRIGGER_SOURCE_EXTERNAL=2, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_TDMA_TRIGGER_SOURCE_SOFTWARE=3} readwrite local 0013158F
"Specifies the source of the trigger signal that starts the frame/slots generation.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_TDMA_TRIGGER_SOURCE_IMMEDIATE 1
The TDMA generator system does not wait for a trigger of any kind, so it is running the frames continuously.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_TDMA_TRIGGER_SOURCE_EXTERNAL 2
Each frame is started with an external signal.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_TDMA_TRIGGER_SOURCE_SOFTWARE 3
Each frame is started with a software programmable trigger."
attribute: "TDMA External Trigger Slope [TDMA]"
	"TDMA:Trigger:TDMA External Trigger Slope [TDMA]"
	iL enum { IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_TDMA_EXTERNAL_TRIGGER_SLOPE_POSITIVE=1, IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_TDMA_EXTERNAL_TRIGGER_SLOPE_NEGATIVE=2} readwrite local 00131590
"Specifies whether the trigger event occurs on the rising or falling edge of the input signal.
IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_TDMA_EXTERNAL_TRIGGER_SLOPE_POSITIVE 1
Enables rising edge triggering.

IVIRFSIGGEN_VAL_TDMA_EXTERNAL_TRIGGER_SLOPE_NEGATIVE 2
Enables falling edge triggering."
